    • Method Detail

      • getDatatype

        java.lang.String getDatatype()
        Returns the datatype of the column values. For wider serialization support it is a string containing the simple name of the datatype class (see Class.getSimpleName()).
        Returns:
        The column datatype

      • getId

        java.lang.String getId()
        Returns the column identifier. This value is application-dependent. It can be something like an integer column index or a database column name, for example. It must be unique so that it can be used to unambiguously identify the referenced column in the model.
        Returns:
        The column identifier
